<body>
    <h1>4. Working with Locations</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p></p>
<div class=3D"toc-macro">
[=20
<a href=3D"#id-4.WorkingwithLocations-AddinganewLocationtoaContent">Adding =
a new Location to a Content</a> ] [=20
<a href=3D"#id-4.WorkingwithLocations-Hide/UnhideLocation">Hide/Unhide Loca=
tion</a> ] [=20
<a href=3D"#id-4.WorkingwithLocations-Deletingalocation">Deleting a locatio=
n</a> ]
</div>
<p></p>
<h2 id=3D"id-4.WorkingwithLocations-AddinganewLocationtoaContent">Adding a =
new Location to a Content</h2>=20
<div class=3D"aui-message hint shadowed information-macro">=20
<p class=3D"title">Full code</p>=20
<span class=3D"aui-icon icon-hint">Icon</span>=20
<div class=3D"message-content">=20
<p><a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/CookbookBundle/blob/master/Comma=
nd/AddLocationToContentCommand.php" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow=
">https://github.com/ezsystems/CookbookBundle/blob/master/Command/AddLocati=
onToContentCommand.php</a></p>=20
</div>=20
</div>=20
<p>We have seen earlier how you can create a Location for a newly created <=
code><a href=3D"http://apidoc.ez.no/sami/trunk/NS/html/eZ/Publish/API/Repos=
itory/Values/Content/Content.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow"=
>Content</a></code>. It is of course also possible to add a new <a href=3D"=
http://apidoc.ez.no/sami/trunk/NS/html/eZ/Publish/API/Repository/Values/Con=
tent/Location.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow"><code>Location=
</code></a> to an existing <code><a href=3D"http://apidoc.ez.no/sami/trunk/=
NS/html/eZ/Publish/API/Repository/Values/Content/Content.html" class=3D"ext=
ernal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Content</a></code>.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"theme: Eclipse; brush: php; gutter: false" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">try
{
    $locationCreateStruct =3D $locationService-&gt;newLocationCreateStruct(=
 $parentLocationId );
    $contentInfo =3D $contentService-&gt;loadContentInfo( $contentId );
    $newLocation =3D $locationService-&gt;createLocation( $contentInfo, $lo=
cationCreateStruct );
    print_r( $newLocation );
}
// Content or location not found
catch ( \eZ\Publish\API\Repository\Exceptions\NotFoundException $e )
{
    $output-&gt;writeln( $e-&gt;getMessage() );
}
// Permission denied
catch ( \eZ\Publish\API\Repository\Exceptions\UnauthorizedException $e )
{
    $output-&gt;writeln( $e-&gt;getMessage() );
}</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>This is the required code. As you can see, both the ContentService and t=
he LocationService are involved. Errors are handled the usual way, by inter=
cepting the Exceptions the used methods may throw.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"theme: Eclipse; brush: php; gutter: false" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">$locationCreateStruct =3D $locationService-&gt;newLocationCreateStr=
uct( $parentLocationId );</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>Like we do when creating a new Content, we need to get a new <code><a hr=
ef=3D"http://apidoc.ez.no/sami/trunk/NS/html/eZ/Publish/API/Repository/Valu=
es/Content/LocationCreateStruct.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofoll=
ow">LocationCreateStruct</a></code>. We will use it to set our new <a href=
=3D"http://apidoc.ez.no/sami/trunk/NS/html/eZ/Publish/API/Repository/Values=
/Content/Location.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow"><code>Loca=
tion</code></a>'s properties. The new Location's parent ID is provided as a=
 parameter to <a href=3D"http://ezsystems.github.com/ezp-next/sami/eZ/Publi=
sh/API/Repository/ContentService#method_newLocationCreateStruct" class=3D"e=
xternal-link" rel=3D"nofollow"></a><code><a href=3D"http://apidoc.ez.no/sam=
i/trunk/NS/html/eZ/Publish/API/Repository/LocationService.html#method_newLo=
cationCreateStruct" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow"><code>Location=
Service::newLocationCreateStruct</code></a></code>.</p>
<p>In this example, we use the default values for the various LocationCreat=
eStruct properties. We could of course have set custom values, like setting=
 the Location as hidden ($location-&gt;hidden =3D true), or changed the rem=
oteId ($location-&gt;remoteId =3D $myRemoteId).</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"theme: Eclipse; brush: php; gutter: false" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">$contentInfo =3D $contentService-&gt;loadContentInfo( $contentId );=
</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>To add a Location to a Content, we need to specify the Content, using a =
<a href=3D"http://apidoc.ez.no/sami/trunk/NS/html/eZ/Publish/API/Repository=
/Values/Content/ContentInfo.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">=
<code>ContentInfo</code></a> object. We load one using <code><a href=3D"htt=
p://apidoc.ez.no/sami/trunk/NS/html/eZ/Publish/API/Repository/ContentServic=
e.html#method_loadContentInfo" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Con=
tentService::loadContentInfo()</a></code>, using the Content ID as the argu=
ment.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"theme: Eclipse; brush: php; gutter: false" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">$newLocation =3D $locationService-&gt;createLocation( $contentInfo,=
 $locationCreateStruct );</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>We finally use LocationService::createLocation(), providing the ContentI=
nfo obtained above, together with our LocationCreateStruct. The method retu=
rns the newly created Location Value Object.</p>
<h2 id=3D"id-4.WorkingwithLocations-Hide/UnhideLocation">Hide/Unhide Locati=
on</h2>=20
<div class=3D"aui-message hint shadowed information-macro">=20
<p class=3D"title">Full code</p>=20
<span class=3D"aui-icon icon-hint">Icon</span>=20
<div class=3D"message-content">=20
<p><a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/CookbookBundle/blob/master/Comma=
nd/HideLocationCommand.php" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https:=
//github.com/ezsystems/CookbookBundle/blob/master/Command/HideLocationComma=
nd.php</a></p>=20
</div>=20
</div>=20
<p>We mentioned earlier that a Location's visibility could be set while cre=
ating the Location, using the hidden property of the LocationCreateStruct. =
Changing a Location's visibility may have a large impact in the Repository:=
 doing so will affect the Location's subtree visibility. For this reason, a=
 LocationUpdateStruct doesn't let you toggle this property. You need to use=
 the LocationService to do so.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"theme: Eclipse; brush: php; gutter: false" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">$hiddenLocation =3D $locationService-&gt;hideLocation( $location );
$unhiddenLocation =3D $locationService-&gt;unhideLocation( $hiddenLocation =
);</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>There are two methods for this: LocationService::hideLocation, and Locat=
ionService::unhideLocation(). Both expect the LocationInfo as their argumen=
t, and return the modified Location Value Object.</p>=20
<div class=3D"aui-message warning shadowed information-macro">=20
<span class=3D"aui-icon icon-warning">Icon</span>=20
<div class=3D"message-content">=20
<p>The explanation above is valid for most Repository objects. Modification=
 of properties that affect other parts of the system will require that you =
use a custom service method.</p>=20
</div>=20
</div>=20
<h2 id=3D"id-4.WorkingwithLocations-Deletingalocation">Deleting a location<=
/h2>
<p>Deleting Locations can be done in two ways: delete, or trash.&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"theme: Eclipse; brush: php; gutter: false" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">$locationService-&gt;deleteLocation( $locationInfo );</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p><a href=3D"http://apidoc.ez.no/sami/trunk/NS/html/eZ/Publish/API/Reposit=
ory/LocationService.html#method_deleteLocation" class=3D"external-link" rel=
=3D"nofollow"><code>LocationService::deleteLocation()</code></a> will perma=
nently delete the Location, as well as all its&nbsp;descendants. Content th=
at have only one Location will be permanently deleted as well. Those with m=
ore than one won't be, as they are still referenced by at least one Locatio=
n.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"theme: Eclipse; brush: php; gutter: false" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">$trashService-&gt;trash( $locationInfo );</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p><code><a href=3D"http://apidoc.ez.no/sami/trunk/NS/html/eZ/Publish/API/R=
epository/TrashService.html#method_trash" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"no=
follow">TrashService::trash()</a></code> will send the Location as well as =
all its descendants to the Trash, where they can be found and restored unti=
l the Trash is emptied. Content isn't affected at all, since it is still re=
ferenced by the trash items.</p>=20
<div class=3D"aui-message warning shadowed information-macro">=20
<span class=3D"aui-icon icon-warning">Icon</span>=20
<div class=3D"message-content">=20
<p>The <code><a href=3D"http://apidoc.ez.no/sami/trunk/NS/html/eZ/Publish/A=
PI/Repository/TrashService.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">T=
rashService</a></code> can be used to list, restore and delete Locations th=
at were previously sent to trash using <a href=3D"http://apidoc.ez.no/sami/=
trunk/NS/html/eZ/Publish/API/Repository/TrashService.html#method_trash" cla=
ss=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow"><code>TrashService::trash()</code></a=
>.</p>=20
</div>=20
</div>
    </div>
</body>
